          Color scheme
        </a>
      </h4>
                    </div>
                    <div id="identity2" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="headingTwo">
                        <div class="panel-body">
                            <p>A Hub colour pallette should be restricted to two primary colours, a ‘brand’ color and an ‘action’ color. This can be extended to a third if necessary.</p>
                            <p>The brand color will be used for text links and detailing.</p>
                            <p>The action color will be used for important links, buttons, and other areas that require the user’s attention. It should be distinguishable from the brand color and will be used sparingly throughout the interface. </p>
                            <p>Colors can be supplied directly as either RGB values or HEX values. If this is not possible or you do not feel comfortable specifying these values, we can extract a color scheme from a logo or image. These 2 colors will be assisted by a range of grey tones (already specified) to aid with visual hierarchy, detailing and typography.</p>
                            <p>You can use this tool to see how your colors comply with web accessibility standards: <a href="http://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/">http://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/</a> </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
